# Essential to know
- Sass/SCSS adds features to CSS (variables, nesting, functions)
- Compiles to regular CSS
- Makes large stylesheets more maintainable
- `.scss` is the most common syntax

---

# Sass/SCSS: Supercharged CSS

## What is Sass?

**Sass** (Syntactically Awesome Style Sheets) extends CSS with:
- Variables
- Nesting
- Mixins (reusable chunks)
- Functions

**SCSS** is Sass with CSS-like syntax (.scss files)

## Why Use It?

**Problem:** CSS gets repetitive
```css
.button-primary { background: #007bff; }
.button-secondary { background: #6c757d; }
.text-primary { color: #007bff; }
```

You're repeating `#007bff` everywhere!

**Solution:** Sass variables
```scss
$primary-color: #007bff;
$secondary-color: #6c757d;

.button-primary { background: $primary-color; }
.button-secondary { background: $secondary-color; }
.text-primary { color: $primary-color; }
```

## Variables

```scss
$font-stack: Helvetica, sans-serif;
$primary-color: #333;
$base-padding: 16px;

body {
  font: 100% $font-stack;
  color: $primary-color;
  padding: $base-padding;
}
```

## Nesting

**CSS (flat):**
```css
nav { background: black; }
nav ul { margin: 0; }
nav ul li { display: inline; }
nav a { color: white; }
```

**SCSS (nested):**
```scss
nav {
  background: black;

  ul {
    margin: 0;

    li {
      display: inline;
    }
  }

  a {
    color: white;
  }
}
```

Much more readable!

## Mixins (Reusable Chunks)

```scss
@mixin border-radius($radius) {
  -webkit-border-radius: $radius;
  -moz-border-radius: $radius;
  border-radius: $radius;
}

.button {
  @include border-radius(4px);
}

.card {
  @include border-radius(8px);
}
```

## Partials & Imports

Split CSS into multiple files:

```scss
// _variables.scss
$primary: #007bff;

// _buttons.scss
.button { background: $primary; }

// main.scss
@import 'variables';
@import 'buttons';
```

## Functions

```scss
@function calculate-rem($pixels) {
  @return $pixels / 16 * 1rem;
}

.text {
  font-size: calculate-rem(24); // 1.5rem
}
```

## Extends

```scss
.message {
  padding: 12px;
  border: 1px solid;
}

.success {
  @extend .message;
  border-color: green;
}

.error {
  @extend .message;
  border-color: red;
}
```

## When to Use Sass?

**✅ Good for:**
- Large projects
- Need to maintain design system
- Working without frameworks
- DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) CSS

**❌ Not needed:**
- Small projects
- Already using Tailwind
- Using CSS-in-JS (styled-components)

lessons.codeExample:
// Real-world SCSS example

// _variables.scss
$colors: (
  primary: #007bff,
  secondary: #6c757d,
  success: #28a745,
  danger: #dc3545
);

$breakpoints: (
  sm: 576px,
  md: 768px,
  lg: 992px
);

// _mixins.scss
@mixin respond-to($breakpoint) {
  @media (min-width: map-get($breakpoints, $breakpoint)) {
    @content;
  }
}

@mixin button-variant($color) {
  background: map-get($colors, $color);
  border: none;
  color: white;
  padding: 12px 24px;
  border-radius: 4px;

  &:hover {
    background: darken(map-get($colors, $color), 10%);
  }
}

// _buttons.scss
.btn {
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.3s;

  &.btn-primary {
    @include button-variant(primary);
  }

  &.btn-danger {
    @include button-variant(danger);
  }
}

// _layout.scss
.container {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 0 15px;

  @include respond-to(md) {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  @include respond-to(lg) {
    max-width: 960px;
  }
}

// main.scss
@import 'variables';
@import 'mixins';
@import 'buttons';
@import 'layout';

